This project implements a smart contactless parking assistance system using an STM32-based trainer kit. It uses an LDR (Light Dependent Resistor) to detect the presence of any obstacles during parking of the vehicle and provides feedback through a buzzer, helping drivers park safely without physical contact. Four conditions were implemented for controlling the frequency of buzzer beeps - 
1-distence less tha 5 cm
2-distance between 5 and 20 cm
3-distance between 20 to 30cm
4-distance greater than 30cm. 
The system is simple, low-cost, and effective for short-range detection.


🎯 Objectives
- To detect vehicle presence using light intensity variation (LDR)
- To process sensor data using STM32 microcontroller
- To alert the driver using a buzzer
- To build a low-cost contactless parking aid system
